        "evidence": "<p>Note: The Basal Energy Expenditure must be multiplied by activity and stress factors to calculate total caloric requirement.</p>\n<p>BEE, kcal/day (male) = 66.5 + (13.75 &times; weight, kg) + (5.003 &times; height, cm) - (6.775 &times; age)</p>\n<p>BEE, kcal/day (female) = 655.1 + (9.563 &times; weight, kg) + (1.850 &times; height, cm) - (4.676 &times; age)</p>\n<p><strong>Harris-Benedict&nbsp;adjustment:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sedentary (little to no exercise) = BEE &times; 1.2</li>\n<li>Light exercise (1-3 days per week) = BEE &times; 1.375</li>\n<li>Moderate exercise (3&ndash;5 days per week) = BEE &times; 1.55</li>\n<li>Heavy exercise (6&ndash;7 days per week) = BEE &times; 1.725</li>\n<li>Very heavy exercise (twice per day, extra heavy workouts) = BEE &times; 1.9</li>\n</ul>",
